tafsir[15]{c,v,t}:
  75,22,"The faces of the people of faith and fortune on that day will be radiant with light."
  75,23,"Looking at their Lord with enjoyment."
  75,24,"The faces of the people of disbelief and wretchedness on that day will be gloomy."
  75,25,"They will be sure that a great punishment and painful punishment is to come down on them."
  75,26,"The matter is not as the idolaters imagined - that they will not be punished when they die. When the soul of any one of them reaches the upper part of his chest."
  75,28,"The person in agony will be certain at that time that this is the departure from the world by death."
  75,29,"Difficulties will come together at the time when the world ends and the afterlife commences."
  75,33,"Then this disbeliever went to his family swaggering in his gait out of pride."
  75,34,"Allah thus warned the disbeliever that His punishment has come close to him."
  75,36,"Does man think that Allah will leave him neglected without imposing any laws on him?"
  75,37,"Was this human being one day not a drop of sperm spilt into the womb."
  75,38,"Thereafter he was a piece of coagulated blood. Then Allah created him and made his form proportionate."
  75,39,"Then he made his species into two types: Male and female?!"
  76,1,"A long period of time has passed over man when he was non-existent and there was no mention of him."
  76,5,"The believers who follow Allah will drink on the day of judgment from a filled cup of wine mixed with camphor because of its pleasant fragrance."